        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">After analyzing fleet data from 200+ HVAC companies, we found that GPS tracking reduces fuel costs by 15-25% and cuts overtime by 20-30%. Here's which solutions deliver the best ROI for different company sizes.</p>

        <h2 id="why-fleet-tracking">Why HVAC Companies Need Fleet GPS Tracking</h2>
        
        <p>HVAC companies face unique fleet challenges. Your technicians drive 150-300 miles daily between service calls, emergency repairs, and equipment deliveries. Without GPS tracking, you're burning money on unnecessary mileage, overtime disputes, and customer complaints about late arrivals.</p>

        <p>The numbers tell the story. HVAC companies using fleet GPS tracking average 18% lower fuel costs, 25% fewer customer complaints about technician arrival times, and 30% reduction in overtime disputes. For a 10-truck operation, this translates to $8,000-15,000 annual savings.</p>

        <p>Modern fleet GPS goes beyond basic location tracking. The best solutions monitor driver behavior (hard braking, speeding, idling), optimize routes in real-time, track equipment temperature for refrigeration trucks, and integrate with your existing <a href="/hvac/dispatch/best-dispatch-software-for-hvac">HVAC dispatch software</a>.</p>

